parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle may stall after fueling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls after fueling
the engine does not start
the vehicle acts as if it is in drive position when it is not.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various warning lights to illuminate, including the check engine light, ABS light, and airbag light, which can be distracting and lead to accidents.
symptoms: The check engine light turns on and off randomly
the speedometer gauges malfunction
the whole panel goes on and off
the automatic sliding doors quit working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the overhead map lights can cause a fire hazard due to arcing or overheating.
symptoms: The overhead map lights stopped working
the light bulb and holder were severely scorched
the plastic was melted and black in color.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger side window motor can cause inconvenience and potentially lead to accidents if the window is stuck in a certain position.
symptoms: The passenger side window motor failed
the window would not roll up or down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The vehicle shutting off while driving can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle completely shut off while driving
the vehicle had to be restarted
the electronics went out
the window with the gear and mileage lights stayed on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition tumbler can cause the vehicle to turn off unexpectedly, leading to loss of brakes and steering, which can be deadly.
symptoms: The ignition tumbler spins very easily
the vehicle can be turned off by just tapping or bumping the bottom of the key
the vehicle turned off while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel tank or fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to potential accidents, especially when driving in heavy traffic or at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls after filling up the gas tank
the engine light comes on
the vehicle hesitates and stalls immediately after a complete fill-up
the vehicle surges forward after filling up gas
the gas cap light and check engine light come on
the vehicle stalls at stop lights or when slowing down to park
the vehicle stalls at high speeds and loses all power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Power steering becomes noisy
loss of power steering
difficulty turning the steering wheel
steering wheel rotates freely but has no effect on vehicle control
vehicle steers to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window switch can cause inconvenience and discomfort, but also poses a safety risk if the driver is unable to roll down the window in an emergency situation.
symptoms: The driver's side window switch seems to be burning out
the window does not roll down
the window has a hard time going back up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the door can cause inconvenience and discomfort, but also poses a safety risk if the door does not open properly, trapping occupants inside.
symptoms: The driver's side passenger van door does not open from the inside
the door has to be opened on the outside
the button on top of the door does not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the 3rd row seat can cause inconvenience and discomfort, but also poses a safety risk if the seat does not stay in place, obstructing the driver's view or causing injury.
symptoms: The 3rd row seat does not stay up
the seat wants to lay down.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.

causing a fire
no warning before the failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling engine can cause loss of control, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
